<paragraph id="8BB1EE5AFFB7C050868CFB85BE30FB85" blockId="6.[151,473,1087,1147]" box="[151,351,1122,1147]" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">
(
<figureCitation id="1335F2DFFFB7C0508684FB85BE6CFB85" box="[159,259,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[247,1334,206,1552]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[235,1353,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Species of Nicolaus. 1 &amp; 2. N. abuensis sp. nov., female; 3 &amp; 4. N. bidentatus sp. nov., male; 5 &amp; 6. N. cornutus sp. nov., male; 7 – 10. Nicolaus bihamatus Xing &amp; Li: 7 &amp; 8. Female from Mudigere; 9 &amp; 10. Male from Shillong." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228653/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">
Figs 
<number id="3DC6FC7DFFB7C05086CCFB85BF8BFB85" box="[215,228,1122,1147]" pageId="6" pageNumber="534" value="5.0">5</number>
–6
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1335F2DFFFB7C0508714FB84BE38FB85" box="[271,343,1123,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 49" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1520,1543]" captionTargetBox="[266,1316,195,1489]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[256,1331,193,1499]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 49. Nicolaus cornutus sp. nov.: 41. Head and thorax, 42. Face; 43 &amp; 44. Male genital capsule, lateral and dorsal views, respectively; 45. Profemur, anterior view as in Rakitov (1998); 46. Valve and subgenital plate, dorsal view; 47. Style, dorsal view; 48. Connective and aedeagus, dorsoanterior view; 49. Connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228657/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">
41– 
<number id="3DC6FC7DFFB7C0508721FB84BE38FB85" box="[314,343,1123,1147]" pageId="6" pageNumber="534" value="49.0">49</number>
</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB1EE5AFFB7C050868CFB4CBE68FAD1" blockId="6.[151,1436,1194,2011]" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">Creamy white. Vertex with pale brown marking on either side of median line; four longitudinal brown stripes on pronotum, inner margins of basal triangle on scutum and veins marked with brown. Face with lateral arcuate stripes meeting median ventrally forked stripe. Femora with brown spot before apex. Some specimens lack brown markings.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB1EE5AFFB7C05086DCFADDBEFCFA89" blockId="6.[151,1436,1194,2011]" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">Head about as long as median length of pronotum. Pronotum about as long as combined median length of scutum and scutellum.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C314BDD1FFB7C05086DCFA64BE72F921" pageId="6" pageNumber="534" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB1EE5AFFB7C05086DCFA64BC4DF9D5" blockId="6.[151,1436,1194,2011]" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis id="B97A3248FFB7C05086DCFA64BE1BFA65" box="[199,372,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with X-shaped sclerotized ridge (
<figureCitation id="1335F2DFFFB7C0508543FA65BCC8FA65" box="[856,935,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 49" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1520,1543]" captionTargetBox="[266,1316,195,1489]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[256,1331,193,1499]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 49. Nicolaus cornutus sp. nov.: 41. Head and thorax, 42. Face; 43 &amp; 44. Male genital capsule, lateral and dorsal views, respectively; 45. Profemur, anterior view as in Rakitov (1998); 46. Valve and subgenital plate, dorsal view; 47. Style, dorsal view; 48. Connective and aedeagus, dorsoanterior view; 49. Connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228657/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">
Fig 
<number id="3DC6FC7DFFB7C050859CFA64BCC8FA65" box="[903,935,1411,1435]" pageId="6" pageNumber="534" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
); caudally narrowed with pair of pigmented denticles. Subgenital plate small, with sclerotized pigmented area along dorsal submargin, posterior margin emarginate. Style without well defined subapical lobe, apophysis simple. Connective very short. Aedeagus robust, shaft membranous, about 
<number id="3DC6FC7DFFB7C05087A5FA09BE80F9F9" box="[446,495,1518,1543]" pageId="6" pageNumber="534" value="0.75">0.75</number>
length of preatrial processes, latter broad at base then narrowed, convexly curved near mid length, apex slightly broadened and foot-shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB1EE5AFFB7C05086DCF9D1BD65F969" blockId="6.[151,1436,1194,2011]" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis id="B97A3248FFB7C05086DCF9D1BEFDF9B0" box="[199,402,1590,1614]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F319AECAFFB7C0508785F9D1BEB9F9B1" box="[414,470,1590,1615]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">Hind</collectingCountry>
margin of seventh sternite medially slightly convexly produced and with median incision. First pair of valvulae gradually narrowed near apex. Second pair of valvulae with teeth placed by distance greater than length of each tooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB1EE5AFFB7C05086DCF944BE72F921" blockId="6.[151,1436,1194,2011]" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis id="B97A3248FFB7C05086DCF944BE1EF944" box="[199,369,1699,1722]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male 
<quantity id="4CF643BFFFB7C05087A1F944BD2DF944" box="[442,578,1699,1723]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.85" metricValueMax="4.9" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="534" unit="mm" value="4.85" valueMax="4.9" valueMin="4.8">4.8–4.9 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity id="4CF643BFFFB7C05084AEF944BC63F944" box="[693,780,1699,1723]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="534" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes. Female 
<quantity id="4CF643BFFFB7C0508226F945BBFBF944" box="[1085,1172,1698,1723]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="534" unit="mm" value="5.1">5.1 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity id="4CF643BFFFB7C050831DF944BA31F944" box="[1286,1374,1699,1723]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="534" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
