<subSubSection id="C314BDD1FFB7C05086DCF89DBE47F824" pageId="6" pageNumber="534" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB1EE5AFFB7C05086DCF89DBE47F824" blockId="6.[151,1436,1194,2011]" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis id="B97A3248FFB7C05086DCF89DBE54F86D" bold="true" box="[199,315,1914,1939]" pageId="6" pageNumber="534">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished by the vertex lacking a submarginal brown stripe between the eyes, the very short connective and the preatrial processes of the aedeagus tapering to a slightly broadened foot– shaped apex.
</paragraph>
